07/06/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov said on Friday (4 June) that NATO would finance a possible enlargement of the Bulgarian mission participating in the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan. 
He said that during his recent visit to Bulgaria, NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer proposed a special arrangement to fund the deployment. 
Sofia also has troops in Iraq.
In other news, EU Enlargement Commissioner Guenter Verheugen begins a two-day official visit to Bulgaria on Monday. 
He is expected to reiterate EU concern over the case of five Bulgarian nurses, sentenced to death in Libya for allegedly spreading the HIV virus. 
(Novinite, news.bg - 07/06/04; Mediapool, Darik - 04/06/04)
